cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.IR. 

The paper discusses a machine learning approach to Relation Extraction, which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also mentions the use of Inductive Logic Programming, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a domain ontology and the storage of extracted relation instances suggest the involvement of databases (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the comparison of OntoILPER with other state-of-the-art RE systems, which indicates the involvement of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG).
